article.description: — Tristan Jarrett had 24 points as Jackson State topped Grambling State 75-61 on Saturday.
article.headline: Jarrett carries Jackson St. over Grambling St. 75-61
article.linkText: Jarrett carries Jackson St. over Grambling St. 75-61
article.story: GRAMBLING, La. -- — Tristan Jarrett had 24 points as Jackson State topped Grambling State 75-61 on Saturday. Jayveous McKinnis had 14 points, 16 rebounds and three blocks for Jackson State (2-5, 2-0 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Isaiah Williams added 12 points and seven rebounds. Jonas James had 10 points. Sarion McGee had 13 points for Grambling State (5-8, 3-3). Trevell Cunningham added 11 points and eight rebounds. Prince Moss had 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
